Privacy Policy for Mobile App Live Streaming Video Sessions 

Effective Date: 29th of Oct 2024 

At iChem, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal 
information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose your 
information when you use our mobile app, particularly during live streaming video sessions 
and Recorded videos. 

By using the app, you consent to the collection and use of information as described in this 
policy. 

1. Information We Collect 

We collect various types of information when you use the app, including: 
  a. Personal Information 
    This is information that identifies you as an individual, such as: 
      • Name 
      • Email address 
      • Phone number 
      • User profile details (including profile photo, username, and bio) 
  b. Usage Data 

We collect data on how you use the app, including: 
      • IP address 
      • Device information (e.g., type, model, operating system) 
      • App usage details (e.g., pages viewed, features used, timestamps) 
      • Log files from live streaming sessions or Recorded Videos 
  c. Content Information 

During live streaming sessions or Recorded videos, we may collect: 
      • Videos, audio, and chat messages shared during the session. 
      • Metadata related to the live stream (e.g., time of stream, participants, duration). 
  d. Cookies and Tracking Technologies 

We may use cookies and similar technologies to improve your experience on the app, track 
usage, and deliver personalized content. You can manage your cookie preferences through 
your device settings. 

2. How We Use Your Information 

  We use the information we collect for the following purposes: 
      • To Provide the Service: Delivering and managing live streaming sessions or 

Recorded Videos, including enabling user interactions, communication, and 
content sharing. 
      • Account Management: Managing your user account and providing you with 
customer support when needed. 
      • App Improvements: Enhancing the app’s functionality, fixing bugs, and improving 
your overall user experience. 
      • Marketing and Communication: With your consent, we may send you marketing 
materials and promotions about features or new programs. You can opt out of these 
communications at any time. 
      • Compliance with Legal Obligations: Ensuring that we comply with applicable 
laws, regulations, and legal processes. 

3. How We Share Your Information 

We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share 
your information in the following circumstances: 
      • Service Providers: We may share your information with third-party vendors, 
consultants, or other service providers who perform services on our behalf (e.g., 
hosting, data analysis, customer support). 
      • Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information to comply with legal 
obligations, such as in response to court orders, government inquiries, or as 
otherwise required by law. 
      • Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your 
information may be transferred as part of the transaction. 

4. Data Security 

We take the security of your personal information seriously and implement appropriate 
measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, loss, or alteration. However, no 
method of data transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 
completely secure, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security. 

5. Data Retention 

We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes 
outlined in this Privacy Policy, or as required by law. After this period, your information will 
be deleted or anonymized. 

6. Your Rights 

Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal 
information, including: 
      • Access: You can request access to the personal information we hold about you. 
      • Correction: You can request that we correct any inaccurate or incomplete personal 
information. 
      • Deletion: You can request that we delete your personal information. 
      • Opt-out: You can opt out of receiving marketing communications from us at any 
time. 

To exercise these rights, please contact us at ichem.dr@gmail.com/+94774857573. 

7. Children’s Privacy 

Our app is not intended for use by children under 10+. We do not knowingly collect 
personal information from children under this age. If you are a parent or guardian and 
believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and 
we will take steps to delete such information. 

8. Third-Party Links and Services 

The app may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for 
the privacy practices of these third parties. We encourage you to review their privacy 
policies before providing any personal information. 

9. Changes to this Privacy Policy 

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted in the 
app, and the revised policy will include the updated "Effective Date." Your continued use of 
the app after any changes indicates your acceptance of the new Privacy Policy. 

10. Contact Us 

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, 
please contact us at: 
Institute of Engineering and Allied Sciences 
iChem Mobile App 
ichem.dr@gmail.com 
+94774857573
